# =============================================================================
# CyberAware frontend — environment variables (Vite)
# =============================================================================
#
# Copy to ONE of these (all gitignored except this example file):
#   • .env              — loaded in all modes
#   • .env.local        — local overrides (recommended for dev)
#   • .env.production.local — test `npm run build` / `vite preview` locally
#
# VITE_API_URL (required for production builds: Vercel, `npm run build`)
#   • Must be the FULL base URL of the FastAPI app INCLUDING the /api prefix.
#   • Local backend default (uvicorn): http://localhost:8000/api
#   • Deployed backend example: https://your-api.up.railway.app/api
#
# Vercel (fixes “VITE_API_URL is not set” on the live site)
#   1. Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#   2. Add VITE_API_URL for Production AND Preview (same value unless you use
#      separate APIs). Value: https://<your-public-backend>/api  (HTTPS)
#   3. Redeploy — Vite bakes env in at build time; changing env requires rebuild.
#
# Monorepo: set Vercel “Root Directory” to Frontend/shieldwise-academy
#
# Backend CORS: set CORS_ORIGINS on the API to include your frontend origin,
# e.g. https://your-app.vercel.app  (see Backend/config.py / .env)
#
# =============================================================================

# Local development (default backend port 8000, routes under /api)
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000/api
